--- [RESPONSE] (22.2s) ---
Based on the detailed requirements, data formats, page designs, and project structure you provided, here is an effective decomposition of the MovieTicketing web application project. This decomposition assigns clear responsibilities to each file/module, aligns with the workflow, and ensures modular, maintainable code.

---

## Overall Project Structure

```
MovieTicketing/
├── app.py                      # Main backend Python app (Flask or similar)
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html          # Movie Dashboard page
│   ├── catalog.html            # Movie Catalog page
│   ├── movie_details.html      # Movie Details page
│   ├── showtimes.html          # Select Showtime page
│   ├── seat_selection.html     # Seat Selection page
│   ├── booking_confirmation.html # Booking Confirmation page
│   ├── booking_history.html    # Booking History page
│   └── theater_information.html# Theater Information page
├── static/
│   ├── styles.css              # CSS styles for all pages
│   └── js/
│       └── scripts.js          # JS for interactivity (seat map, filters)
└── data/
    ├── movies.txt              # Movie data
    ├── theaters.txt            # Theater data
    ├── showtimes.txt           # Showtimes data
    ├── seats.txt               # Seats data
    ├── bookings.txt            # Bookings data
    └── genres.txt              # Genres data
```

---

## Decomposition of Tasks and File Responsibilities

### 1. `app.py` — Backend Application Logic

**Responsibilities:**

- Serve all frontend pages via routes.
- Read and write all data files (`movies.txt`, `theaters.txt`, `showtimes.txt`, `seats.txt`, `bookings.txt`, `genres.txt`) locally.
- Implement all business logic:
  - Load and parse data files into appropriate data structures.
  - Handle search, filter, and pagination for movies and theaters.
  - Manage showtime selection and filtering.
  - Manage seat availability and booking status updates.
  - Handle booking confirmation and persist bookings.
  - Provide booking history filtered by status.
- Provide data to frontend templates via context variables.
- Handle form submissions and button actions (e.g., booking confirmation, filtering).
- Run the web server on a local port, accessible via browser.

**Key subtasks:**

- Implement route `/dashboard` → render `dashboard.html` with featured movies and quick links.
- Implement route `/catalog` → render `catalog.html` with search and genre filter.
- Implement route `/movie/<movie_id>` → render `movie_details.html` with movie info.
- Implement route `/showtimes/<movie_id>` → render `showtimes.html` with showtimes filtered by theater and date.
- Implement route `/seats/<showtime_id>` → render `seat_selection.html` with interactive seat map.
- Implement route `/booking_confirmation` → render `booking_confirmation.html` and handle booking submission.
- Implement route `/booking_history` → render `booking_history.html` with bookings table and status filter.
- Implement route `/theaters` → render `theater_information.html` with theater list and location filter.

---

### 2. Frontend Templates (HTML files in `templates/`)

Each HTML file corresponds to a single page as per requirements. They use templating (e.g., Jinja2 if Flask) to dynamically display data passed from `app.py`.

- **`dashboard.html`**
  - Container div with ID `dashboard-page`.
  - Display featured upcoming releases.
  - Buttons: `view-bookings-button`, `showtimes-button`.

- **`catalog.html`**
  - Container div with ID `catalog-page`.
  - Search input with ID `search-input`.
  - Genre filter dropdown with ID `genre-filter`.
  - Movie cards grid with movie poster, title, duration.
  - Each movie card has a button `view-movie-button-{movie_id}`.

- **`movie_details.html`**
  - Container div with ID `movie-details-page`.
  - Display movie title (`movie-title`), director (`movie-director`), rating (`movie-rating`), description (`movie-description`).
  - Button to proceed to showtime selection.

- **`showtimes.html`**
  - Container div with ID `showtimes-list`.
  - Theater filter dropdown with ID `theater-filter`.
  - Date picker input with ID `date-filter`.
  - List of showtimes with time, theater, price.
  - Button to select showtime.

- **`seat_selection.html`**
  - Container div with ID `seat-selection-page`.
  - Interactive seat map div with ID `seat-map`.
  - Div to display selected seats with ID `selected-seats-display`.
  - Button `proceed-booking-button` to confirm seat selection.

- **`booking_confirmation.html`**
  - Container div with ID `confirmation-page`.
  - Booking summary div with ID `booking-summary`.
  - Input field for customer name/email with ID `customer-email`.
  - Button `confirm-booking-button` to finalize booking.

- **`booking_history.html`**
  - Table with ID `bookings-table` showing booking info.
  - Status filter dropdown with ID `status-filter`.
  - Buttons `view-booking-button-{booking_id}` for each booking.
  - Button `back-to-dashboard` to return.

- **`theater_information.html`**
  - Container div with ID `theater-info-page`.
  - Theater list div with ID `theaters-list`.
  - Location filter dropdown with ID `theater-location-filter`.
  - Button to navigate back to dashboard.

---

### 3. Static Files

- **`styles.css`**
  - Common styles for layout, colors, fonts, buttons, grids.
  - Responsive design for seat map and movie cards.

- **`js/scripts.js`**
  - Interactive seat map logic (select/deselect seats, update selected seats display).
  - Filters for genres, theaters, booking status.
  - Event handlers for buttons and dropdowns.
  - Any AJAX calls if needed (optional, can be done via full page reloads).

---

### 4. Data Files (`data/`)

- **`movies.txt`**
  - Store movie_id, title, director, description, release_date, rating, genre(s).

- **`theaters.txt`**
  - Store theater_id, name, location, city, number_of_screens, facilities.

- **`showtimes.txt`**
  - Store showtime_id, movie_id, theater_id, showtime_date, showtime_time, price, available_seats.

- **`seats.txt`**
  - Store seat_id, theater_id, screen_id, row, column, seat_type, status (Available/Booked).

- **`bookings.txt`**
  - Store booking_id, showtime_id, customer_name, customer_email, booking_date, total_price, status, seat_list.

- **`genres.txt`**
  - List of genres for filtering.

---

## Workflow Circles (Dependencies)

1. **Data Loading & Parsing** (app.py)
   - Load all data files into memory on app start or per request.
2. **Dashboard & Catalog Pages**
   - Use movie and genre data.
3. **Movie Details Page**
   - Use movie data.
4. **Showtimes Page**
   - Use showtimes, theaters, and movie data.
5. **Seat Selection Page**
   - Use seats and showtime data.
6. **Booking Confirmation**
   - Use booking data and update bookings.txt.
7. **Booking History**
   - Use bookings.txt filtered by customer or status.
8. **Theater Information**
   - Use theaters.txt and filter by location.

---

## Summary Table of Files and Responsibilities

| File                      | Responsibility Summary                                  | Backend / Frontend |
|---------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|--------------------|
| `app.py`                  | Main backend logic, routing, data handling             | Backend            |
| `templates/dashboard.html`| Dashboard page UI                                       | Frontend           |
| `templates/catalog.html`  | Movie catalog UI with search/filter                     | Frontend           |
| `templates/movie_details.html` | Movie details UI                                   | Frontend           |
| `templates/showtimes.html`| Showtimes selection UI                                  | Frontend           |
| `templates/seat_selection.html` | Seat selection UI                                 | Frontend           |
| `templates/booking_confirmation.html` | Booking confirmation UI                      | Frontend           |
| `templates/booking_history.html` | Booking history UI                                | Frontend           |
| `templates/theater_information.html` | Theater info UI                                | Frontend           |
| `static/styles.css`        | CSS styles                                             | Frontend           |
| `static/js/scripts.js`     | JS interactivity                                       | Frontend           |
| `data/movies.txt`          | Movie data storage                                     | Data file          |
| `data/theaters.txt`        | Theater data storage                                   | Data file          |
| `data/showtimes.txt`       | Showtimes data storage                                 | Data file          |
| `data/seats.txt`           | Seats data storage                                    | Data file          |
| `data/bookings.txt`        | Bookings data storage                                 | Data file          |
| `data/genres.txt`          | Genres list                                           | Data file          |

---

## Additional Notes

- Each HTML page should be self-contained with proper IDs and classes as per requirements.
- Backend must ensure data consistency when updating bookings and seat statuses.
- No encryption or external DB; all data read/written as plain text files.
- The app should be runnable locally with a single command (e.g., `python app.py`).
- Frontend JS should enhance UX but not required for core functionality.
- Clear comments and modular functions in `app.py` for maintainability.

---

This decomposition breaks down the project into manageable, single-responsibility files and tasks, enabling parallel development and clear ownership. It aligns with your requirements and ensures a smooth workflow from data handling to UI rendering and user interaction.
